# Area Pages SEO

When editing area pages or AreaDetail.jsx:

- **Schema**: Each area must have unique LocalBusiness and Service JSON-LD. Use the area’s own `area.name` and `area.postcodes` in areaServed/serviceArea (e.g. Keynsham + BS31, Bath + BA1/BA2). Keep @id per-slug (e.g. `#localbusiness-{slug}`).
- **Metadata**: Title and meta description must include the specific town name and "Website Designer" where relevant. Keep areaMeta.js in sync with areasData metaTitle/metaDescription.
- **Content**: Prefer a distinct "Why choose SEO Kings in [Town Name]" (or equivalent) per area to avoid duplicate content; use area-specific copy, landmarks, or stats.
- **Links**: Include a clear link back to the homepage and links to nearby areas (e.g. nearbyAreas) for crawlability.
- **Constraints**: Do not change CSS theme or layout; only change SEO metadata, schema, and location-specific strings.
